We have made some further changes for you:

  1. Events page: https://msra.org.au/events
  2. Conferences and workshops page: https://msra.org.au/conferences-and-workshops/

We are currently working on it. Here's a page that we created: https://msra.org.au/conferences-and-workshops-2/ . Can you please check if that's what you are asking for? We are not able to find the previous MS Research Conference so that's what we put in there.

Hi Rica,

Could you please let me know the status of the below?

I also wanted to check to see if you have put the redirect in place?

This is what I sent through last Friday:

Firstly, the new conference website URL is: https://www.ivvy.com.au/event/MSRA21/register.html. Could you please create a URL for us and point to the new conference website URL? We are happy to have a URL similar to last time e.g. https://msra.org.au/event/ms-research-conference-2021/.

Secondly, could you please updated our page: https://msra.org.au/conferences-and-workshops/ with the attached assets) and title of "Progress in MS Research Scientific Conference 2021" and include a "Register Now" button. I have attached a few assets that could work as background images, however please let me know if these images do not work for this and I can send you something else.

We urgently need this set up as this is to go live before Friday. Please let me know if you have any questions.

Kind regards,

Jess

Hi Heath,


Happy Friday 😊


Similar to past years, we are quickly organising a website for our 2021 Progress in MS Scientific Conference.


Trish has let me know that you kindly assisted us in 2019 to set up a redirect and update the https://msra.org.au/conferences-and-workshops/ page with new assets and link to the conference website page.


Firstly, the new conference website URL is: https://www.ivvy.com.au/event/MSRA21/register.html. Could you please create a URL for us and point to the new conference website URL? We are happy to have a URL similar to last time e.g. https://msra.org.au/event/ms-research-conference-2021/.


Secondly, could you please updated our page: https://msra.org.au/conferences-and-workshops/ with the attached assets) and title of "Progress in MS Research Scientific Conference 2021" and include a "Register Now" button. I have attached a few assets that could work as background images, however please let me know if these images do not work for this and I can send you something else.


We are happy for this to be live now.


Please let me know if you have any questions regarding any of the above.


Kind regards,
Jess
